00:20:59.014 --> 00:21:03.284
like shifting the focus
to adapting to the disability,

00:21:03.285 --> 00:21:06.935
instead of the barriers
within the application.

00:21:07.422 --> 00:21:10.991
Let's try to simulate a barrier
which does not require

00:21:10.992 --> 00:21:14.721
the user to take
on a different kind of persona.

00:21:15.096 --> 00:21:17.131
What if we designed an application

00:21:17.132 --> 00:21:20.034
that worked perfectly
for narrow viewports,

00:21:20.035 --> 00:21:21.602
but is completely broken

00:21:21.603 --> 00:21:25.094
when viewed on a standard
widescreen display?

00:21:26.174 --> 00:21:28.276
Something like this.

00:21:29.644 --> 00:21:32.580
I am showing a video,
where the content shifts

00:21:32.581 --> 00:21:37.017
or disappears unpredictably
in a widescreen format,

00:21:37.018 --> 00:21:40.826
but it is completely
fine in the narrow viewport.

00:21:48.396 --> 00:21:51.565
Why do I think
this approach is better?

00:21:51.566 --> 00:21:55.069
Well, for a start,
it hits people without forcing them

00:21:55.070 --> 00:21:57.137
to change their perspective.

00:21:57.138 --> 00:22:00.342
It hits them at home, so to speak.

00:22:00.642 --> 00:22:04.178
Users don't have to pretend
to be someone else.

00:22:04.179 --> 00:22:09.016
They just experience frustration
the way they naturally browse.

00:22:09.017 --> 00:22:12.920
They get to experience the feeling
of getting into a digital experience

00:22:12.921 --> 00:22:16.557
which works as it should,
and does what it says, yet,

00:22:16.558 --> 00:22:18.259
it is not designed for them,

00:22:18.260 --> 00:22:21.496
and therefore,
does not work for them.

00:22:22.230 --> 00:22:23.998
The problem isn't them.

00:22:23.999 --> 00:22:26.067
It's the broken design.

00:22:28.570 --> 00:22:33.374
Instead of thinking, "Wow, being
visually impaired must be hard,"

00:22:33.375 --> 00:22:35.654
and pitying disabled people,

00:22:35.655 --> 00:22:39.380
they think, "Wow,
this layout is terrible.

00:22:39.381 --> 00:22:42.108
Now, I am furious at bad design."

00:22:43.652 --> 00:22:48.730
The focus stays on fixing the system,
not adapting to disability.

00:22:49.691 --> 00:22:53.420
One leads to charity,
the other leads to change.

00:22:55.997 --> 00:22:57.431
You shouldn't need to pretend

00:22:57.432 --> 00:23:00.764
to be disabled to care
about accessibility.

